# Boss Relationship Tracker - Cursor Rules

## Tech Stack
- React Native + Expo + TypeScript
- Expo Router for file-based navigation
- Firebase: Firestore, Auth, FCM, Cloud Functions
- Mobile-first (iOS + Android)

## Code Style
- **TypeScript required** - strict typing for all code
- Use functional components with hooks
- Type all props, state, and function returns
- Follow Expo Router file-based routing conventions

## Project Structure
- `app/` - routing and screens
- `components/` - reusable UI components
- `services/` - Firebase services (auth, firestore, notifications)
- `types/` - TypeScript type definitions
- `utils/` - helper functions
- `functions/` - Firebase Cloud Functions

## Firebase Data Model
- Users: `/users/{userId}`
- Bosses: `/users/{userId}/bosses/{bossId}`
- Entries: `/users/{userId}/bosses/{bossId}/entries/{entryId}`
- Entry types: `note`, `survey`, `interaction`

## Security
- Always ensure user data access is scoped to `userId`
- Firebase rules enforce `request.auth.uid === userId`
- Never expose other users' data

## Best Practices
- Use Expo SDK for native features (notifications, etc.)
- Handle authentication state properly
- Type Firebase documents with TypeScript interfaces
- Test on both iOS and Android when possible

